The government wants to limit the torture of &quot;witches&quot;, it has published a brochure
Women declared witches in Burkina Faso tend to have several commonalities.
Rather, they belong to the older generation, they cannot participate in work, for example for health reasons, they are single and have no children.
The one who &quot;becomes&quot; a witch is sent into isolation so as not to endanger the rest of the village.
&quot;A man rarely catches this fate.&quot;
&quot;Even healthy young women are not relegated because they help with work and give birth to children,&quot; said a nun who cared for more than a hundred women expelled from their ranks in a special home in the West African capital of Burkina Faso.
