About 44% of respondents across the region expressed satisfaction with the way democracy works in practice in their country, the same figure as last year, but a large increase compared to 2001, when it was 25% ( graph 3).
Roughly 34% said they trust the parliament in their country and 45% trust the government, again the same figures as last year, but a big difference compared to 2003 (17% and 24%).
Ten years ago, democracy in Latin America was undermined by the economic crisis.
